0th.270: In preparation for the Beef Empire Days Rodeo parade, young girls practice for a performance under the tall grain elevator along the railroad tracks.  Corn was taken out town to sell all over the world, but now these tracks bring corn TO Garden City, Kansas  for the feedlots that ring the area.
